{"lemma":"مَحْرَمِ","slug":"مَحْرَمِ","root":"ح.ر.م","root_slug":"ح-ر-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَحْرَمِ","root":"حرم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7779","n7780","n7782"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"forbidden"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Muharram (the first month of the Islamic calendar, when many Islamic communities hold a festival commemorating the deaths of the grandsons of Muhammad)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of حَرَّمَ (ḥarrama, “to forbid”); compare حَرَام (ḥarām, “forbidden”).\n\nFrom الْمُحَرَّم (al-muḥarram, “the forbidden”), from الشَّهْر الْمُحَرَّم (aš-šahr al-muḥarram), literally \"the forbidden month\", for being one of the four months in which Arabs forbade fighting, a tradition continued in Islam. The month is of special importance for Shia Muslims, for being the month in which the Battle of Karbala occurred."},"ipa":["/mu.ħar.ram/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7779","headword_ar":"مَحْرَمٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraAmN","text_ar":"حَرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with which it is syn. (S, Mgh, Msb.) [And see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~N","text_ar":"حَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A female relation whom it is unlawful to marry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a male relation"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise:] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHimo maHoramN","text_ar":"رَحِمْ مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relationship that renders it unlawful to marry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa lahu maHoramN","text_ar":"هِىَ لَهُ مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is a relation to him such as it is unlawful for him to marry"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa lahaA maHoramN","text_ar":"هُوَ لَهَا مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa maHoramu minohaA","text_ar":"هُوَ مَحْرَمُ مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uw maHoramK minohaA","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُو مَحْرَمٍ مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is one whom it is unlawful for her to marry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw raHimK","text_ar":"ذُو رَحِمٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramK","text_ar":"مَحْرَمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw raHimK maHoramN","text_ar":"ذُو رَحِمٍ مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHrm","text_ar":"محرم"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHm","text_ar":"رحم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*w","text_ar":"ذو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlqaraAbapi","text_ar":"فِى القَرَابَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapK","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 669:) and in the case of a woman,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu raHimK maHoramK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ رَحِمٍ مَحْرَمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArimu All~ayoli","text_ar":"مَحَارِمُ اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fearful places of the night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the coward is forbidden to traverse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxaArimu","text_ar":"مَخَارِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoramN","text_ar":"مَخْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["T","Msb","Mgh","S","IAar","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n7780","headword_ar":"مُحْرِمٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraAmN","text_ar":"حَرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHil~N","text_ar":"مُحِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and as such signifying [also] one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with whom it is unlawful to fight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or, as such,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whom it is unlawful to slay:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hl","text_ar":"حل"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and, as such also, one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has a claim,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenanted right, to protection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safeguard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hl","text_ar":"حل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) Er-Rá'ee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qataluwA A@boni Eaf~aAna Alxaliyfapa muHorimFA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They slew"},{"kind":"text","text":"('Othmán)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ibn-' Affán, the Khaleefeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"while entitled to the respect due to the office of Imám and to the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sacred"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"city and to the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sacred"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"month:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for he was slain [in ElMedeeneh and] in [the month of] Dhu-l-Hijjeh. (Ham p. 310.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lamuHorimu Eanoka","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَمُحْرِمُ عَنْكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one whom it is unlawful for thee to harm:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for whom it is unlawful to harm thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Th:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whom it is unlawful for thee to harm and for whom it is unlawful to harm thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musolimN muHorimN","text_ar":"مُسْلِمٌ مُحْرِمٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Muslim is secure, as to himself and his property, by the respect that is due to El-Islám:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a Muslim refrains from the property of a Muslim, and his honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation, and his blood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is at peace with another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.) ―         -b3-  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hariym","text_ar":"حَرِيم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa muHorimN binaA","text_ar":"هُوَ مُحْرِمٌ بِنَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is in our"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hariym","text_ar":"حَرِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fasting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a faster:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the faster is prohibited from doing that which would break his fast. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And, for a like reason,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Swear ing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a swearer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","IAar","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n7782","headword_ar":"مُحَرَّمٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Forbidden, prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made un lawful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced, sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in violable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entitled to reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA Ealimota A^an~a AlS~uwrapa","text_ar":"اَمَا عَلِمْتَ اَنَّ الصُّورَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amapu","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowest thou not that the face is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbidden to be beaten?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that it has a title to reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHar~amu","text_ar":"المُحَرَّمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first of the months"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, * TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the year"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Arabs"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"since the age of pagan ism"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"being prefixed because it is originally an epithet; but accord. to some, it is not prefixed to the name of any other month; or, accord. to some, it may be prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sfr","text_ar":"صفر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$w~Al","text_ar":"شوّال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the age of paganism, the seventh month, also called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoru A@ll~`hi AlA^aSab~u","text_ar":"شَهْرُ ا@للّٰهِ الاَصَبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlASb~","text_ar":"الاصبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being app. a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSam~u","text_ar":"الاَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajabN","text_ar":"رَجَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [for] Az says, the Arabs used to call the month of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajab","text_ar":"رَجَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the age of paganism,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSam~u","text_ar":"الاَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHar~amu","text_ar":"المُحَرَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he cites the saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aqamonaA bihaA $ahoraYo rabiyEK kilaAhumaA\n                      \n                     \n                        wa$ahoraYo jumaAdaY waA@sotaHal~uwA AlmuHar~amaA"},{"kind":"page_break","n":557},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We stayed in it during the two months of Rabeea, both of them, and the two months of Jumádà; and they made El-Moharram to be profane;"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. by postponing it, as the pagan Arabs often did]: the Arabs called it thus because they did not allow fighting in it [unless they had postponed it]: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amaAtN","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArimu","text_ar":"مَحَارِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAriymu","text_ar":"مَحَارِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaramN","text_ar":"حَرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"—"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amN","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a camel means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"untractable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or,] thus applied, [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruwDN","text_ar":"عَرُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive in the middle part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult to be turned about,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stubborn in the head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when turned about:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~aluwlu AlwasaTu","text_ar":"الذَّلُولُ الوَسَطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~aluwlu AlwasaTi","text_ar":"الذَّلُولُ الوَسَطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in my MS. copy of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~aluwlu","text_ar":"الذَّلُولُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwasT","text_ar":"الوَسط"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not broken, or not trained:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not yet completely broken or trained:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amapu AlZ~ahori","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمَةُ الظَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a she-camel that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"untractable; not broken, or not trained:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense heard by Az from the Arabs. (TA.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  A skin"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not tanned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not completely tanned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tanned, but not made soft, and not thoroughly done."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"new"},{"kind":"text","text":"whip: (K:) or a whip"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not yet made soft."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)  An Arab of the desert"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rude in nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition, chaste in speech, that has not mixed with people of the towns or villages."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the nose"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is soft in the hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","K","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}